text.tspan: User Problems
•I have to keep track of so many username and passwords for different
applications, so I write them all down.
•We use so many different applications for work, it is difficult to keep track
of what I do and do not have access to.
•I lose productivity, since I can't use my own phone or tablet to work when
I'm outside the office.
•I forget my password frequently, since I am required to create a complex
password and change it often.
Business problems
•It is becoming increasingly difficult to provide employees seamless access
to all the cloud based applications that our business has signed up to.
•The need to provide consistent and secure access to mobile applications
on different platforms is a challenge many IT departments are not currently
equipped to handle.
•Keeping track of and managing devices being used to access work
resources has now become very difficult with the increasing numbers of
employees doing work using their personal computer, tablet, or phone.
•Reducing the risks involved with user's passwords being compromised will
often involve sacrificing usability by forcing users to create complex
passwords or implementing a complex and expensive two factor validation
infrastructure.
Solution
"I can work anywhere, anytime and using any device"
•Employees use one credential to easily access all their work resources,
improving user experience and eliminating the need to store passwords in
insecure ways.
•Access to applications can be easily provided to all types of work or
personal mobile devices, and reduces data leaks by keeping your data
inside work applications away from the user's personal applications.
•Computers, phones, and tablets of all types can be consistently secured so
that employees can work anywhere, anytime and with any device.
•Two factor validation adds an additional layer of protection to your
applications and reduces the risks of unauthorised access to your data due
to compromised passwords.
